# Copy to .env (git-ignored). Pipeline, semantic-review, and serving entrypoints
# forward their declared values with modal.Secret.from_dotenv. The Hebrew v3
# OpenAI producer deliberately uses the named secrets documented below instead.
# Credentials are never written to public artifacts, and the redaction scanner
# keeps their values out of logs and reports.

# Hugging Face read token with access to the configured base model. Keep this
# remote-runtime token read-only. An executed Hub publication should inject a
# separate least-privilege write token as HF_TOKEN only on the release host.
HF_TOKEN=

# OpenAI key with Responses access for the one-time Hebrew v3 dataset teacher.
# This value is not auto-forwarded. Provision the provider boundary once with:
#   uv run modal secret create openai-api-key OPENAI_API_KEY="$OPENAI_API_KEY"
#   uv run modal secret create huggingface-read-token HF_TOKEN="$HF_TOKEN"
# The full translation requires both exact named secrets.
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Optional: require this value as a Bearer token on the vLLM serving
# endpoint (remote_serving.py). Without it the endpoint is open.
# SOMMELIER_SERVE_API_KEY=

# Optional: wandb key for opt-in experiment tracking.
# WANDB_API_KEY=
